pageContext.claim: “So I never met Carter Page. I think to this day I never met Carter Page. I never met Carter Page. [George] Papadopoulos, I never met him, other than one time, where he sat at a table along with maybe 10 or 15 other people, because they wanted to set up a national security team.”
pageContext.analysis: Page and Papadopoulous were two of the first three names Trump volunteered when asked to name foreign-policy advisers during a 2016 interview with The Washington Post's editorial board.
